author: Lilith Rochas
title: Your stars with Lilith
text:
Your stars 
This week's sun in sultry Scorpio and Tuesday full moon in pleasure-loving Taurus invite us to smell the flowers, eat the sweets and enjoy life's unending smorgasbord …
*ARIES: Early week's lunar activity could trigger a startling realisation which you feel deeply and respond to strongly. Focus on opportunity rather than loss, on moving forward towards solutions rather than staying locked in problems. Then, since energy flows where attention goes, new offers start popping up like mushrooms. Happy now? 
*TAURUS: This week's Tauran high point is Tuesday's full moon in your sign, a powerful supermoon which asks if your deep needs are being recognised. Which, of course, isn't anyone else's job but yours. Check in on what Bob Dylan calls that 'restless, hungry feeling', which is usually for soul food and emotional nourishment. 
*GEMINI: This week's security-seeking full moon has important information for you about where you aren't listening to your inner Twin. Set sensible goals by all means, but try to order your priorities so they're more in alignment with your heart's desires. Once you make the choice, existence steps in to assist. 
Advertisement *CANCER: Rough and tumble Aries moon, intense Taurus supermoon, hectic Gemini moon… this week's emotional ebbs and surges suggest that you get as much wind-down, decompression time as possible. And even though holding on is what you're excellent at, be advised that letting go is currently the wiser course. 
*LEO: With your ruling planet moving into a fellow fixed-sign, it's worthwhile speaking less and listening more. Being flexible – especially when it's in your interests to let someone else win. Capitalise on this week's advantageous career stars with strategic moves; you enjoy competition, but no need to make war.  
*VIRGO: Mars in Virgo wants to change the world. Jupiter in Virgo wants to educate the world. Venus in Virgo wants personal housekeeping: a self-enquiry into redecorating your room for improvement. Regarding all of which, does it really matter whether the glass is half full or half empty? Isn't it refillable?  
*LIBRA: With your planet ruler Venus supporting energetic Mars and confidence-booster Jupiter in the sort-it-out sign of do the right thing, this busy week presses the start button on something you haven't been quite ready till now to take on. Beneficial connections with like-minded others are beckoning.
*SCORPIO: As the sun shines its light on your happy birthday month and personal zone of leadership, this week highlights all the progress you've made in mastering Saturn's two-year long, hard look at yourself, and sometimes gruelling boot camp. Now the identity crisis is over, it's time for reinvention… 
*SAGITTARIUS: Saturn in your sign for the coming couple of years challenges you to identify weak links in your operating techniques that need developing, plus any tiny minor flaws in your awesome personality that may need refining. Sagittarius and Saturn are both teachers, so this week features themes of education and professional development. 
*CAPRICORN: As your ruling planet Saturn takes up residence in Capricorn's twelfth house of slowdown and healing forgiveness, get ready for a reflective three-year exploration of the inner you – along with the possible sacrifice of some part of your persona. If you've experienced a loss, this week offers therapeutic closure. 
*AQUARIUS: Yes, you space cadets are made of star stuff ... whose current address is earth, where accounts need to be paid. Sharing resources may make that easier to achieve this week – which is a good one for acknowledging the valuable contributions a partner, friend, group or mentor has made in your life. 
*PISCES: For your mutable sign, the present Saturn cycle initiates a long-term total restructure of your personal and professional life to a newer, more mature shape. As this week's planetary emphasis in your partnership zone begins the slow, thorough makeover, charm won't be as effective an accessory as honesty.
